feat(security): add CSRF protection and nonce-based CSP (S7, S8)

S7 – CSRF protection:
- Generate per-session CSRF token (secrets.token_hex(32))
- Validate X-CSRF-Token header on all POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints
- Templates include <meta name="csrf-token"> for JS fetch calls
- All fetch() calls in index.html and admin.html send the header

S8 – Nonce-based CSP (replaces unsafe-inline):
- Generate per-request CSP nonce via secrets.token_urlsafe(16)
- <style> and <script> tags in both templates use nonce="{{ csp_nonce }}"
- CSP header uses 'nonce-{nonce}' for script-src and style-src
- Falls back to 'unsafe-inline' when nonce is unavailable

Tests:
- 8 new dedicated CSRF tests (test_csrf.py)
- CSP nonce assertion in test_routes.py
- Autouse fixture bypasses CSRF for existing tests; CSRF tests re-enable it
- All 79 tests pass
